.IX Item "--flavors-from=FILE , -fFILE"
Use flavor heuristics from \s-1FILE\s0 (default=built\-in).
.Sp
Default: '\s-1NULL\s0'
.Sp
If specified, \s-1FILE\s0 should be a flavor definition file containing a list of regular-expression based token classification rules
to be used in computing special entries for the lexical frequency file.
See \fImootfiles\fR\|(5) for a full specification of the moot flavor definition file format.
If unspecified, the default behavior is to use a built-in set of classification heuristics.
If \s-1FILE\s0 is an empty string, no flavor heuristics at all will be applied.
